The paper focuses on developing an unsupervised neural network approach for learning embedding representation for a collection of graphs, which can be used in various graph mining tasks such as clustering, visualization, and classification. This work involves machine learning techniques and deals with graph data, which are common themes in several arXiv CS sub-categories. Based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
